# tools/ota_publish.env.example — infra config template for ota_publish.sh
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy to a GIT-IGNORED sibling and fill in YOUR real values:
#     cp tools/ota_publish.env.example tools/ota_publish.env
#     $EDITOR tools/ota_publish.env
# ota_publish.sh sources `tools/ota_publish.env` automatically if present (dotenv-style),
# so you never retype the host/broker/addon overrides. This .example ships PLACEHOLDERS
# only (the repo is public); the real `tools/ota_publish.env` is in .gitignore — same
# pattern as rust/clock/src/{secrets,board}.rs. The broker PASSWORD is NEVER stored here:
# ota_publish.sh sources it live from the Mosquitto/JuicePassProxy addon option.
#
# Plain shell assignments (this file is `.`-sourced). Leave a line unset/commented to fall
# back to the script's placeholder default (or a pre-set environment variable).

OTA_HOST_SSH=<ssh-host>        # ssh alias for the image host (scp target), e.g. an entry in ~/.ssh/config
OTA_HOST_IP=<image-host-ip>    # image host IP on the boards' own VLAN (same subnet as the boards)
OTA_PORT=8087                  # smol-ota static HTTP server port (default 8087)
BROKER=<broker-ip>             # Mosquitto broker leg reachable from where you run this
MQTT_USER=<mqtt-user>          # broker username (password is sourced live from the addon, not here)
ADDON=<addon-slug>             # Supervisor addon slug that carries mqtt_password
